This paper deals with the problem of estimating a sparse vector in the linear model, which is a fundamental problem in signal processing, statistics, and compressive sensing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also discusses the performance of compressive sensing techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SP (Signal Processing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper establishes a lower bound on the mean-squared error, which involves optimization and numerical analysis, indicating that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical aspects of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
